 during class hour to learn from Pallas more about the promotion campaign  for learning \"弟子規\".\r\n\r\nWe will also pass out the New Year Party DVDs. I am really amazed by the way the videos are edited. JauYeu Lai did an outstanding job and please, let\'s all give him a huge applause.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 舒志翔, 李青\r\n\r\nBest Regards\r\nAlex Tang\r\nPrincipal, MCS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Communication - 3/6/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-communication-362010','','','2010-03-05 00:57:39','2010-03-05 04:57:39','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=46',0,'post','',0),(47,1,'2010-03-12 23:04:09','2010-03-13 03:04:09','Dear MCS parents,\r\n\r\nLast week Mrs. Pallas Wang 杜愛白 女士 donated $970 to our school to support scholarship system we instituted this year. She also decided to sponsor scholarship to students who may recite 弟子規. According to her suggestion, the awarding policy has been changed to the following:\r\n\r\nThere are 6 sections in 弟子規. Students may get $10 award for each section he or she recited. Students who may recite the complete 弟子規 will be awarded $100. Recitation may begin on the week of 5/15. Scholarship will be awarded during the school graduation ceremony.\r\n\r\nHere\'s the link to an ROC government website that has very helpful teaching material of 弟子規: <a href=\"http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/\" target=\"_blank\">http://edu.ocac.gov.tw/biweekly/classics/</a>\r\n\r\nThis week we will have Chinese SAT II mock up test. Please remind your kids who have registered for the test come to school on time with their own 2B pencil and eraser on Saturday.  The test will be held at 1:30PM in Room 2401. Students who are in either Ma-Li-Ping classes or senior class and not taking the test, should take the 7th grade class instead.\r\n\r\nParents on duty: 王鴻烈 &amp;                王武駒\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will deliver your Chinese food 