ale continue on this Saturday</em></span></strong></div>\r\n<div>(3)Free adult <strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (注音符號) </strong>class enrollment at parents lounge. Class starts on 10/2</div>\r\n<div>(4)Food service on Saturday 9/25: QQ 麵包, 雞腿便當, 肉圓 ,炒米粉 ,竽頭酥, 滷雞腿 ....等. Quantity is limited.</div>\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\r\n<div><a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a></div>','MCS Newsletter - 9/25/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','ncs-newsletter-9252010','','','2010-10-28 12:20:16','2010-10-28 16:20:16','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=92',0,'post','',0),(93,1,'2010-09-22 22:24:17','2010-09-23 02:24:17','','NCS Newsletter - 9/25/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','92-revision','','','2010-09-22 22:24:17','2010-09-23 02:24:17','',92,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=93',0,'revision','',0),(94,1,'2010-09-30 22:23:06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">MCS PTA</span></strong>\n\nCongratulations to 陸樹德-new elected 2010-2011 PTA president and 王棋洲 -Vice President.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Budget, Donation &amp; Fun Raising</span></strong>\n\nDuring our parents meeting last week, each staff presented the work plan for school year 2010-2011 and the budget. There are two major reasons caused we face financial challenge. First, this year we had fewer students which is a common concern for all other Chinese Schools in Metro area. Second, we used to have a great amount of our parents’ donation through United Way and this income for sure has come to an end.\n\nMichigan Chinese School is a non-profit organization and your donation can be tax deductible. Every dollar you donate to Michigan Chinese School will be 100% spent on students’ education. If you already have had United Way donation set up at work, you may think about moving all or portion of your donation direct to Michigan Chinese School . You will receive the tax deductible letter from the School. Parent Thomas Sheng suggested setting up an automatic donation from bank account monthly. Our staff is working on this and will keep everyone posted when further information becomes available.\n\nIf you have any fun raising ideas, please contact out staff.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Adult </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Mandarin</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Phonetic Symbols</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> (</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">注音符號</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">) </span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">class </span></strong>\n\nClass will start this Saturday at 1:30 pm in room 2407.\n\nInstructor: Lisa Hou\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Evacuation Drill</strong></span>\n\nScheduled on October 9, 2010\nJesse Wei\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School\n\n<a href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/</a>','MCS Newsletter -10/2/2010',0,'','draft','open','open','','','','','2010-09-30 22:23:06','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=94',0,'post','',0),(95,1,'2010-10-13 23:18:30','2010-10-14 03:18:30','<div><span style=\"font-size: small;\">First of all, we would like to thank <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Brian and Linda Shu</span></strong> who donate their referral cash award to school. </span></div>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fire Drill</span></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Just a reminder, we will have our annual fire drill this Saturday. All students, teachers and parents who are on campus must participate this drill. See attached map for stair near by your classroom. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Directory Advertisements</span></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">If you know anyone who is interested to have advertisements on our directory, please talk to any staff. This could be a helpful income for school.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Hunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\">Jesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School</span>','MCS Newsletter -10/9/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-10162010','','','2010-10-13 23:21:44','2010-10-14 03:21:44','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=95',0,'post','',0),(96,1,'2010-10-13 23:18:05','2010-10-14 03:18:05','','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','95-revision','','','2010-10-13 23:18:05','2010-10-14 03:18:05','',95,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=96',0,'revision','',0),(97,1,'2010-10-13 23:18:30','2010-10-14 03:18:30','Donation\r\n\r\nThanks to Poyu &amp; Limei Tsou\'s generous donation to Michigan Chinese School .\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFire Drill\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful fire drill last week. In case there is an emergency in the future, please follow the path to a safe location.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFund Raising\r\n\r\nQQ bakery.  Starts at 1:15 pm this Saturday 10/16.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSpecial Event\r\n\r\n(1)   MCAPA 密西根國建學術聯誼會2010 年會邀請函\r\n\r\n– see attached flyer \"MCAPA2010_80-20_v3.pdf\"\r\n\r\n(2)   第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法 – see attached file \"第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法.doc\"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nEmployment Opportunity\r\n\r\nIndiana University Bloomington .  The Department of East Asian Languages &amp; Cultures seeks to fill a full-time lecturer position in Chinese language to begin in fall 2011.\r\n\r\nSee attached file \"Employment.doc\"\r\n\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','95-revision-2','','','2010-10-13 23:18:30','2010-10-14 03:18:30','',95,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=97',0,'revision','',0),(98,1,'2010-10-13 23:22:27','2010-10-14 03:22:27','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Donation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Poyu &amp; Limei Tsou\'s generous donation to Michigan Chinese School .\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fire Drill</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful fire drill last week. In case there is an emergency in the future, please follow the path to a safe location.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\nQQ bakery.  Starts at 1:15 pm this Saturday 10/16.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Special Event</span></strong>\r\n\r\n(1)   MCAPA 密西根國建學術聯誼會<strong>2010 </strong>年會邀請函\r\n\r\n– see attached flyer \"<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">MCAPA2010_80-20_v3.pdf</span>\"\r\n\r\n(2)   第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法 – see attached file \"<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">第一屆華文文化歌唱觀摩實施辦法.doc\"</span>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Employment Opportunity</span></strong>\r\n\r\nIndiana University Bloomington .  The Department of East Asian Languages &amp; Cultures seeks to fill a full-time lecturer position in Chinese language to begin in fall 2011.\r\n\r\nSee attached file \"<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Employment.doc</span>\"\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-10162010-2','','','2010-10-13 23:22:27','2010-10-14 03:22:27','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=98',0,'post','',0),(99,1,'2010-10-13 23:22:06','2010-10-14 03:22:06','','MCS Newsletter -10/16/2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','98-revision','','','2010-10-13 23:22:06','2010-10-14 03:22:06','',98,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=99',0,'revision','',0),(100,1,'2010-10-22 22:19:13','2010-10-23 02:19:13','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s(侯珞怡) dedicated hard work to provide free teaching about <strong><strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (</strong></strong><strong><strong>注音符號</strong></strong><strong><strong>)</strong></strong> to MCS parents. School will send out survey to those adult students and if there is a need, we will consider offering a new tuition based adult CSL class.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Budget</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAfter parents meeting on 9/25/2010, some of you show the concern about our school budget not balanced from previous school year. There was a different between school account balance on 6/30/2010 and bank statement at that time. Jointed efforts was made by 2009-2010 Principal Tang (唐宗堯), current staff Jessica Lee (陳惠昭)and Chih-Wen Pai (白志文) and finally we have balanced the budget. When MCS started offering Ma Li-Ping classes back to several years ago, initially school purchased more teaching material than actually need in order to get the volume discount. At that time school counted it as an asset. Ideally, we will have to offset it when it was sold, but school counted it as an income. Therefore, there is a difference between school balance sheet and bank statement. We will have this issue corrected this year. We also will present this to parents Rep. during New Year Party preparation meeting (新年晚會籌備會議) scheduled on Nov.6. Everyone is welcomed to attend.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Halloween Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBased on our survey from each class, the majority prefer to have school wide Halloween Party as usual. We will have our 2010 Halloween Party on October 30 during the recess. If you have any Halloween decoration stuff that you can support this event, please let any staff or myself know. Any new Halloween decoration ideas? Please share it with us.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Reading Month</span></strong>\r\n\r\nReading month will start on Oct. 30 and end on Dec. 4. Please find attached form for your child/children\'s record. If you have any questions, please talk to your teacher.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance</span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS will continue award students with perfect attendance each semester. To be considered perfect attendance, absence per week <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">CAN NOT</span> be longer than 15 minutes.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Funding Raising</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Jitai &amp; Long-Hua Jhou (周治太, 駱龍華) picked up the bakery from QQ last week. We had an excellent bake sale and every thing was sold out within 15 mins. For those who came to parents lounge and didn\'t get any, we will have more next time.\r\n\r\nBake Sale: 3<sup>rd</sup> week on each month\r\n\r\nJesse Wei\r\nPrincipal, Michigan Chinese School','MCS Newsletter -10/23/2010',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-10232010','','','2010-10-22 22:19:13','2010-10-23 02:19:13','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=100',0,'post','',0),(101,1,'2010-10-22 22:19:01','2010-10-23 02:19:01','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Lisa Hou\'s(侯珞怡) dedicated hard work to provide free teaching about <strong><strong>Mandarin Phonetic Symbols (</strong></strong><strong><strong>注音符號</strong></strong><strong><strong>)</strong></strong> to MCS parents. School will send out survey to those adult students and if there is a need, we will consider offering a new tuition based adult CSL class.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Budget</span></strong>\n\nAfter parents meeting on 9/25/2010, some of