周年的第一天,密西根僑民將於元月一日上午十一點,在美華中心廣場舉行密西根的升旗典禮(全球以美國加州時間早上八點為準),希望台灣僑民們踴躍參加,也歡迎攜帶美國當地朋友參加,升旗典禮過後,於12點籌備會將提供多種粥點,以祛寒氣,希望僑學各界能多多呼朋引友踴躍參加,也希望鼓勵年輕學子參與.\n\n時間 : 元月一日上午十一點,\n\n地點 : 美華活動中心廣場:32585 Concord Drive, Madison Hts., MI 48071\n\n有問題者可洽: 周綵玲2483208888孫絡典5868263936\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Holidays Break</span></strong>\n\nThere will be no school for 12/25/2010 and 1/1/2011, due to holidays break. We  wish your family the gifts of joy, good health and peace this  season. We wish you warm wonderful times with family and friends and  much love. We look forward to exciting and challenging new learning  experiences in the 2011 New Year!','MCS Newsletter     Dec. 18, 2010',0,'','inherit','open','open','','116-revision','','','2010-12-16 18:10:06','2010-12-16 22:10:06','',116,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=117',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Happy New Year</span></strong>\r\n\r\nI hope all of you enjoyed the holiday break and spent some relaxing time with friends and family.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Communication</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAs  we discussed at beginning of school year, we would like to promote  email communication between teachers and parents/students so that we can  save paper and protect environment. Teachers will send out weekly  teaching progress and homework assignment by email. If you don’t have  computer to access these communication, you can stop by Madonna  University library during our regular school hours and there are many  computers available.\r\n\r\nWhile  I organized our school contact directory, I noticed that several  families were not on the weekly newsletter distribution list. If you  didn\'t receive our weekly newsletters in the past, you can go to school  website for archive information.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Teachers Survey</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  had reviewed the survey result with each teacher individually on  12/18/2010. This survey served as a bridge between teachers and  parents/students and we will conduct another survey on later part of  this school year.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Pre-Register for 2<sup>nd</sup> semester </span></strong>\r\n\r\nPre-register  for next semester will begin this week (1/8) and end on (1/15). You can  save $20.00 for each student, if you pre-register. It\'s school policy  that if you do not pre-register, <strong><em>you will be charged $20.00 registration fee for each student you enroll.</em></strong><strong> </strong>Registration form is attached and also available on school website.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011\r\n\r\nTickets on sale: 1/8/2011. Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Calendars</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe  will have some 2011 calendars from Taiwan available this Saturday at  parents lounge. Limited quantity and first come first serve.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-8-2011','','','2011-01-08 00:23:08','2011-01-08 04:23:08','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=118',0,'post','',0),(119,1,'2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','','MCS Newsletter        Jan. 8, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','118-revision','','','2011-01-08 00:22:43','2011-01-08 04:22:43','',118,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=119',0,'revision','',0),(120,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up the bakery from QQ bakery last week.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Spring 2010-2011</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis  weekend will be the beginning of Spring 2010-2011 semester. Welcome  those new students and families. Because New Year Party is scheduled  next week, <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">we will have after school curriculums this week for those who need more practice.</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEvent Date: Saturday, 1/29/2011 at 2:30 pm\r\n\r\nTickets on sale now: Adults: $10.00, Students: $5.00\r\n\r\nNew Year Party is <strong><em>one </em></strong>event includes students\' performance and dinner.\r\n\r\nWe are highly encouraging all school members to invite friends and families to celebrate the year of rabbit.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">New Year Party Last Preparation Meeting</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe will have one more meeting for all parents rep\'s from each class and staff this week to make sure we have everything covered.\r\n\r\nLocation: Parents Lounge\r\n\r\nTime: 1:45pm','MCS Newsletter  Jan. 22, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-jan-22-2011','','','2011-01-20 00:10:38','2011-01-20 04:10:38','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=120',0,'post','',0),(121,1,'2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','','MCS Newsletter  ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','120-revision','','','2011-01-20 00:10:05','2011-01-20 04:10:05','',120,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=121',0,'revision','',0),(122,1,'2011-02-03 21:27:54','2011-02-04 01:27:54','<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Rose Geist (尹新妹) generous donation to Michigan Chinese School.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had a very successful New Year Party on Jan.29 at Stevenson High School. Thanks to all teachers and students\' hard work to practice their entertainment program. Also thanks to all staff and parents who spent so much efforts and time on this event. Without your support, we won\'t have this annual event.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures/DVD</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe had two photographers Hank Kwong (鄺力衡) and Sylvia Richards (劉蔚芝) taking pictures in this event. Hank had all his photos ready in the following link and Sylvia will have her photos ready soon. We will also have links add to school website for your viewing purpose. Feel free to download the pictures you like and thanks to them when you meet them next time.\r\n\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email</a>\r\n\r\nIf you want to purchase a copy of New Year Party DVD, please sign in this Saturday at Parent\'s Lounge. $5.00 only.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">張奶奶壓歲錢</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThis will be distributed during class this Saturday. Students/Parents don\'t forget to thank 張奶奶\r\n\r\nnext time when you see her.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Academic Excellent Award</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom. Only for classes that teacher provided the list.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Spring After School Curriculum Registration</span></strong>\r\n\r\nRegistration will begin this week.','MCS Newsletter    Feb.5, 2011 ',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-5-2011','','','2011-02-03 21:27:54','2011-02-04 01:27:54','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=122',0,'post','',0),(123,1,'2011-02-03 21:27:41','2011-02-04 01:27:41','<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Rose Geist (尹新妹) generous donation to Michigan Chinese School.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party</span></strong>\n\nWe had a very successful New Year Party on Jan.29 at Stevenson High School. Thanks to all teachers and students\' hard work to practice their entertainment program. Also thanks to all staff and parents who spent so much efforts and time on this event. Without your support, we won\'t have this annual event.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures/DVD</span></strong>\n\nWe had two photographers Hank Kwong (鄺力衡) and Sylvia Richards (劉蔚芝) taking pictures in this event. Hank had all his photos ready in the following link and Sylvia will have her photos ready soon. We will also have links add to school website for your viewing purpose. Feel free to download the pictures you like and thanks to them when you meet them next time.\n\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email\" target=\"_blank\">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/sredir?uname=hank.n.michelle&amp;target=ALBUM&amp;id=5567814662483572449&amp;authkey=Gv1sRgCJylxImLiaiYdQ&amp;invite=CJvk34wG&amp;feat=email</a>\n\nIf you want to purchase a copy of New Year Party DVD, please sign in this Saturday at Parent\'s Lounge. $5.00 only.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">張奶奶壓歲錢</span></strong>\n\nThis will be distributed during class this Saturday. Students/Parents don\'t forget to thank 張奶奶\n\nnext time when you see her.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Academic Excellent Award</span></strong>\n\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom. Only for classes that teacher provided the list.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Spring After School Curriculum Registration</span></strong>\n\nRegistration will begin this week.','MCS Newsletter    Feb.5, 2011 ',0,'','inherit','open','open','','122-revision','','','2011-02-03 21:27:41','2011-02-04 01:27:41','',122,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=123',0,'revision','',0),(124,1,'2011-02-09 21:30:59','2011-02-10 01:30:59','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures from Sylvia Richards (</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">劉蔚芝</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">)</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Sylvia providing the following link to view all pictures she took on 1/29.\r\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink\" target=\"_blank\">https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Video</span></strong>\r\n\r\nEntire program DVD is available for you to own with cost of $5.00.  Sing up sheet is in parents lounge.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance Award</span></strong>\r\n\r\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Movie </span></strong>\r\n\r\nStudents (鄺紹耘, 王淨德, 王淨慧, 邱晧)  from our school took part in the movie Smooch.  It will be showing on  Hallmark channel on 2/11 at 9:00 pm and 2/12 at 3:00 pm.\r\n\r\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter          Feb.12, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-12-2011','','','2011-02-09 21:30:59','2011-02-10 01:30:59','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=124',0,'post','',0),(125,1,'2011-02-09 21:30:46','2011-02-10 01:30:46','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Pictures from Sylvia Richards (</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">劉蔚芝</span></strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">)</span></strong>\n\nThanks to Sylvia providing the following link to view all pictures she took on 1/29.\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink\" target=\"_blank\">https://picasaweb.google.com/snap2shot/20110129MCSChineseNewYearParty?authkey=Gv1sRgCM3MjLexmb6b4wE&amp;feat=directlink</a>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Video</span></strong>\n\nEntire program DVD is available for you to own with cost of $5.00.  Sing up sheet is in parents lounge.\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Perfect Attendance Award</span></strong>\n\nAward will be given to students this week at each classroom.\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong></strong>\n\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Movie </span></strong>\n\nStudents (鄺紹耘, 王淨德, 王淨慧, 邱晧)  from our school took part in the movie Smooch.  It will be showing on  Hallmark channel on 2/11 at 9:00 pm and 2/12 at 3:00 pm.\n\nHunan-Hunan will be on campus this Saturday; you may place your order in advance and pick up at school.','MCS Newsletter          Feb.12, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','124-revision','','','2011-02-09 21:30:46','2011-02-10 01:30:46','',124,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=125',0,'revision','',0),(126,1,'2011-02-16 14:15:29','2011-02-16 18:15:29','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Vicky Lin (林曉君) Valentine\'s sweet sale last week and all sales donated to school.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Message from Madonna University </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMadonna University  reported there was equipment damage recently in one of our classrooms.  It\'s hard to believe this was conducted by our students/teachers unless  they can provide evidence. But I would like to emphasize and remind you  the following:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>All  equipment in each classroom is for teaching purpose. It\'s not a toy,  nor game. Madonna University provides us an excellent learning  environment.</li>\r\n	<li>Students <strong><em><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">shouldn\'t</span></em></strong> play with in classroom equipment unless it is under teacher\'s supervision and for study purpose only.</li>\r\n	<li>Parents,  please communicate with your child/children that don\'t stay in  classroom or play with computer equipment after regular school hour.</li>\r\n	<li>At the end of class, please return everything back to its original location. You moved it and you put it back.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2011 Chinese New Year Party Video/DVD</span></strong>\r\n\r\nFor those who signed up to purchase 2011 New Year Party DVD, please come to parents lounge at first hour to pick up your DVD. The cost is $5.00. Thanks to Jauyeu Lai (賴昭宇) spent a lot of personal time to make this happen.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">School Website </span></strong>\r\n\r\nHave you visited our school website lately? <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.michiganchineseschool.org/\" target=\"_blank\">www.michiganchineseschool.org</a>\r\n\r\nThanks to Steven Lien who updated the pictures and 2011 New Year Party pictures links.\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fund Raising </span></strong>\r\n\r\nIt\'s 3<sup>rd</sup> Saturday again. As usual, we will have QQ bakery as our school fund raising. Don\'t miss it and be there in time.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Winter Break </span></strong>\r\n\r\nThere will be no school next Saturday (2/26/2011), due to winter break. Wish ever family has a relaxed and safe break.','MCS Newsletter     Feb.19, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-feb-19-2011','','','2011-02-16 14:15:29','2011-02-16 18:15:29','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=126',0,'post','',0),(127,1,'2011-02-16 14:14:45','2011-02-16 18:14:45','','MCS Newsletter     Feb.19, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','126-revision','','','2011-02-16 14:14:45','2011-02-16 18:14:45','',126,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=127',0,'revision','',0),(128,1,'2011-03-02 20:35:15','2011-03-03 00:35:15','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up QQ bakery last time and made our fund raising successful.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration is begun. Parents please encourage your child/children to participate and help them to practice. If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first. If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Promotion </span></strong>\r\n\r\nOne of our 2010-2011 directory sponsors – hair stylist Ms. Noel Leung will be at parents lounge this Saturday with fliers from her hair salon.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 School Directory Amendment</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe have several new families jointed us this semester and attached is the directory supplemental.\r\n\r\nChinChen Burkholder (黃勤珍) will have bakery for sales this week at parents lounge.','MCS Newsletter  March 5, 2011',0,'','publish','closed','open','','mcs-newsletter-march-5-2011','','','2011-03-02 20:35:51','2011-03-03 00:35:51','',0,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=128',0,'post','',0),(129,1,'2011-03-02 20:34:55','2011-03-03 00:34:55','','MCS Newsletter  March 5, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','128-revision','','','2011-03-02 20:34:55','2011-03-03 00:34:55','',128,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=129',0,'revision','',0),(130,1,'2011-03-02 20:35:15','2011-03-03 00:35:15','<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Appreciation</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThanks to Kevin Wang (王惠章) picking up QQ bakery last time and made our fund raising successful.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Speech Contest </span></strong>\r\n\r\nMCS speech contest is scheduled on 4/9 and registration is begun. Parents please encourage your child/children to participate and help them to practice. If any parents need extra support, please talk to your teacher first. If additional support is needed, please contact Mei-Ying Huang (教務主任- 黃玫瑛).\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Promotion </span></strong>\r\n\r\nOne of our 2010-2011 directory sponsors – hair stylist Ms. Noel Leung will be at parents lounge this Saturday with fliers from her hair salon.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2010-2011 School Directory Amendment</span></strong>\r\n\r\nWe have several new families jointed us this semester and attached is the directory supplemental.\r\n\r\nChinChen Burkholder (黃勤珍) will have bakery for sales this week at parents lounge.','MCS Newsletter  March 5, 2011',0,'','inherit','open','open','','128-revision-2','','','2011-03-02 20:35:15','2011-03-03 00:35:15','',128,'http://michiganchineseschool.org/blog/?p=130',0,'revision','',0);
